title: We are not under Premier League’s strings – ANC Women’s League
text:
The ANC Women’s League has vehemently denied the allegation that its strings are being pulled by the so-called Premier League in the ANC.
The league was addressing media at Gallagher Estate in Midrand a day before the organisation heads to the National General Council.
Secretary-General Meogo Matuba said there was no such thing as the Premier League in the ANC structures.
She said the current leadership was elected in a democratic process at its recent elective conference.
